        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 4:30PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 430 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Buckhannon, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Philippi, Audra State Park, Volga, Hodgesville, and Century.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
